The global brain vasculitis market is expected to witness significant growth by 2028, driven by various factors such as an increase in the prevalence of autoimmune diseases leading to brain vasculitis, advancements in diagnostic techniques, and the rising adoption of immunosuppressive therapies. The primary angiitis of the central nervous system (PACNS) segment is anticipated to dominate the market due to the high incidence of this disease. Additionally, the imaging tests in the diagnosis segment are expected to gain traction owing to their accuracy in detecting vasculitis in the brain. In terms of treatment, corticosteroids are widely prescribed, but the demand for advanced therapies like rituximab is projected to increase in the forecast period. Hospitals are the primary end-users of brain vasculitis treatment, providing advanced care facilities for patients.

